1772629924768155	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3kgs		item.create	bn-2fzw	{"description":"## Problem\n\nWhen the TUI's periodic refresh fires (`tick()`), it calls `reload()` which calls `try_open_projection()` → `ensure_projection()` → `incremental_apply()` → `rebuild::rebuild()`. Every step uses `?` with no error catch, so if the rebuild fails for any reason (corrupt shard, parse error, disk issue) the error propagates all the way up and crashes the TUI — even though the TUI was doing nothing but passively refreshing its read-only view.\n\n## Error chain\n\n```\nmod.rs:129  app.tick()?\nmod.rs:61     list_view.tick()\nlist.rs:2991    self.reload()?\nlist.rs:1817      try_open_projection(&self.db_path)?\nquery.rs:896        ensure_projection(bones_dir)?\ndb/mod.rs:92          incremental_apply(...).context(\"auto-rebuild projection\")?\nincremental.rs:412      rebuild::rebuild(...).context(\"full rebuild during incremental apply fallback\")?\nrebuild.rs:134            anyhow::bail!(\"parse error at line {line_no}: {e}\")\n```\n\n## Fix\n\nIn `list_view.tick()` (list.rs ~line 2991), catch the reload error instead of propagating it:\n\n```rust\npub fn tick(&mut self) -> Result<()> {\n    if self.last_refresh.elapsed() >= self.refresh_interval {\n        if let Err(e) = self.reload() {\n            self.set_status(format!(\"DB refresh failed: {e:#}\"));\n        }\n        self.last_refresh = std::time::Instant::now();\n    }\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThis keeps the TUI alive, shows the error in the status bar, and retries on the next tick interval (so it will recover automatically if the condition is transient).\n\nAlso check the initial load in `ListView::new()` (list.rs ~line 1811): `view.reload()?` at construction time — this also crashes if the projection can't be built on startup. Consider handling that too: start with an empty list and show the error in the status bar rather than failing to open the TUI at all.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `ws/default/crates/bones-cli/src/tui/list.rs`: `tick()` and `ListView::new()`\n- Possibly `ws/default/crates/bones-cli/src/tui/triage.rs`: `TriageView::new()` and `reload()` calls there if the same pattern applies\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Running `bn ui` with a corrupt/unrebuildable projection shows an error in the status bar instead of crashing\n- The TUI retries the rebuild on the next tick (currently every few seconds)\n- If the projection recovers (e.g. user fixes the shard file externally), the TUI picks it up automatically on the next successful tick","kind":"task","title":"TUI should not crash when periodic DB rebuild fails"}	blake3:8hfHMeNZBi3bsEDqv7dcsTvHdgk8S3KcRyq93Kb_jM0
1772630376280498	bob	itc:v3:AWKSc8kyZJPJk5EAAAAAQau9WtV610AAAAEzeQ		item.create	bn-817g	{"description":"- use nesting with the same nesting rules\nfor --format pretty:\n- use the same unicode glyphs and colors\nfor --format text:\n- use G for goal, T for task, B for bug\n- use the text sizes in brackets if set ([s], [xl])\n- no colors or glyphs\n- have a legend (G=Goal, T=Task, B=Bug)\n- use [urgent] or [punted] if those apply\n\nhere's a snip of the ui\n\n│ ◇ bn-27z Phase A: Skeleton + Deterministic Runner                                                                            │\n│   ▷ bn-1lr ⠉ Rust project scaffold + CI [foundation] [phase-a]                                                               │\n│     ▷ bn-3jt ⠛ sigil.toml config parser [foundation] [phase-a]                                                               │\n│       ▷ bn-rdc ⠉ sigil init: project scaffolding command                                                                     │\n│       ▷ bn-1rt ⠉ Risk classification: file-path heuristics → R0-R3 risk class [phase-a] [policy]                             │\n│         ▷ bn-3fw ⠉ Simple threshold policy: sigil decide [phase-a] [policy]                                                  │\n│           ▷ bn-2yu ⠉ GitHub Actions sigil-action wrapper [ci] [phase-a]                                                      │\n│       ▷ bn-2l7 ⠉ Artifact resolution: PR ref → Docker image digest [eval] [phase-a]                                          │\n│       ▷ bn-3hu ⠁ Deploy recipe hash: compute + record for reproducibility tuple [deploy] [phase-a]                           │\n│         ▷ bn-z4b ⠛ Eval report generation + ledger events [eval] [phase-a]                                                   │\n│           ▷ bn-og9 ⠉ Fail-closed degradation tests: verify BLOCK/REVIEW on every failure mode [phase-a] [security] […        │\n│           ▷ bn-14r ⠉ Lossy feedback generator [feedback] [phase-a]                                                           │\n│           ▷ bn-352 ⠉ Isolation wall invariant tests: verify no holdout content leaks [phase-a] [security] […                 │\n│       ▷ bn-12t ⠉ Age encryption/decryption for holdout scenarios [encryption] [phase-a]…                                     │\n│         ▷ bn-3r0 ⠁ Holdout review bot workflow [ci] [phase-a] [securi…                                                       │\n│         ▷ bn-3r6 ⠉ Scenario management CLI [cli] [phase-a] [scena…                                                           │\n│         ▷ bn-2o7 ⠁ TTY gate + audit logging for holdout access [phase-a] [scenario] […                                       │\n│         ▷ bn-1iz ⠁ Audit log completeness test: verify all security events logged [phase-a] [security] […                    │\n│       ▷ bn-pui ⠉ Scenario discovery + loading [phase-a] [scenario]                                                           │\n│       ▷ bn-3vm ⠉ Control-ref snapshot + scenario set loading [eval] [phase-a]                                                │\n│       ▷ bn-j0b ⠉ GitLedger: file-based append + git sync [ledger] [phase-a]                                                  │\n│         ▷ bn-31h ⠉ SQLite ledger projection + incremental replay [ledger] [phase-a]                                          │\n│         ▷ bn-12s ⠉ Ledger integration test: concurrent writers + projection convergence [ledger] [phase-a] [te…              │\n│       ▷ bn-xzs ⠉ Key management CLI [cli] [encryption] [ph…                                                                  │\n│       ▷ bn-38s ⠉ sigil doctor: dependency and config health checks [cli] [phase-a]                                           │\n│     ▷ bn-272 ⠉ External runner subprocess contract: sigil-runner-* protocol [phase-a] [runner]                               │\n│     ▷ bn-2bz ⠉ Assertion library: expect.* API [phase-a] [runtime]                                                           │\n│       ▷ bn-12q ⠛ Property testing: sigil.property() with generator composition + shrinking [phase-a] [runtime]               │\n│       ▷ bn-2xr ⠉ Host globals injection: sigil.* Lua API surface [phase-a] [runtime]                                         │\n│         ▷ bn-67m ⠉ CLI runner: sigil.exec [phase-a] [runner]                                                                 │\n│         ▷ bn-17g ⠉ HTTP client: sigil.get/post/put/patch/delete [phase-a] [runner]                                           │\n│           ▷ bn-zgk ⠁ HTTP request/response capture for artifacts [phase-a] [runner]                                          │\n│         ▷ bn-3hm ⠉ Scenario execution: load + run + collect results [phase-a] [runtime]                                      │\n│         ▷ bn-1l3 ⠉ sigil scenario run: local development scenario runner [cli] [phase-a] [runti…                             │\n│     ▷ bn-mzi ⠉ full-moon Lua parser integration [phase-a] [scenario]                                                         │\n│       ▷ bn-3nq ⠉ Doc comment extraction from AST [phase-a] [scenario]                                                        │\n│         ▷ bn-17r ⠉ AST metadata extraction + validate + lint [phase-a] [scenario]                                            │\n│           ▷ bn-1tl ⠉ mlua sandbox setup + module restrictions [phase-a] [runtime]                                            │\n│             ▷ bn-3sx ⠉ Scenario execution loop: run scenarios against environments [eval] [phase-a]                          │\n│               ▷ bn-3p5 ⠉ Baseline comparison + satisfaction scoring [eval] [phase-a]                                         │\n│     ▷ bn-1sg ⠁ Event types + Ledger trait definition [ledger] [phase-a]                                                      │\n│       ▷ bn-etu ⠉ Phase A property tests: scoring, RNG determinism, TSJSON [phase-a] [test]                                   │","kind":"task","title":"bn triage graph should look like the execution sort in the ui"}	blake3:GDanGCF5_fVK8t3VyDMBc9bDpnRcYDprxteNwXgRkgk
