1772646620669337	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3ogs		item.create	bn-61tl	{"description":"The current.events symlink/forwarding-pointer is the root cause of the shard corruption bug. active_shard() already uses list_shards().last() — the symlink is never read at runtime. Remove update_symlink entirely, stop creating current.events in bn init, add current.events to .gitignore, delete read_forwarding_pointer (keep as skip logic during replay for existing corrupted repos). Remove all tests that assert symlink existence.","kind":"task","title":"Remove current.events symlink, derive active shard from sorted filenames"}	blake3:YZv872BGddyjiOcOrwq9FavF8J51DfA23NyrEynShbw
1772646626571825	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3ows		item.create	bn-22s7	{"description":"Before replay, check each sealed shard's byte length and blake3 hash against its .manifest file. If they don't match, warn loudly and skip the corrupted shard (or bail). This catches any form of shard corruption — not just forwarding pointers. The manifest already records event_count, byte_len, and file_hash. Add a validate_manifest() call to ShardLineIterator initialization.","kind":"task","title":"Validate sealed shard manifests on startup"}	blake3:-9-w9jzAA1Hyj4OeM44r_YLrOkkUXkO5bsg-HsBXnOU
1772646633379170	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3pAs		item.create	bn-n5dz	{"description":"Before appending to or reading from a shard file, verify the first line is '# bones event log v1'. A 14-byte forwarding pointer or any other non-event content would fail this check immediately. Add a check in open_shard_for_append() and in ShardLineIterator when opening each shard file. This is a fast sanity check that prevents writing events into a corrupted file.","kind":"task","title":"Validate shard header before append or read"}	blake3:pFDp8byDTo-OYMSI_MCEkoxryFAeWR95DXK385JrWQI
1772646640125054	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3pQs		item.create	bn-3pge	{"description":"A bn doctor (or bn verify) command that validates all shards against manifests, checks that the active shard has a valid header, detects orphaned events (item.move without item.create), and reports any anomalies. Should be runnable as a periodic health check. Could also check for duplicate event hashes, out-of-order timestamps, and parse errors across all shards.","kind":"task","title":"Add bn doctor command for integrity verification"}	blake3:XTNA2bPN50brr34qr7wtsTT3KJWlqLJhN168mtEjNFA
